{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, we found that discourse segmentation was performed in two studies.",
    "This task divides texts into coherent segments such as sentences, paragraphs, or topics, which helps to structure the text and generate items in a way that reflects the logical and semantic composition of the input texts.",
    "Furthermore, label extraction assigns labels to texts according to categories like reading difficulty, content domain, or question type.",
    "The extracted labels serve as control labels for creating targeted and relevant items.",
    "For example, Zhao et al. (2022) trained an LLM to extract one of the seven question types based on input texts, aiding in generating questions that match the intended type."
  ]
}